  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the <strong>air fryer </strong>to 200°C</p><p>Add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675272404032-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675272404032-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675272404032-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675272404032-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675272404032-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and cut the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</strong> </span>into quarters, then separate the wedges so you end up with a pile of onion petals</p><p>Chop the <strong>orange<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>in half</p><p>Cut the <strong>broccoli</strong> into small florets, discard the stem and leaves</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675272410652-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675272410652-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675272410652-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675272410652-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675272410652-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a splash of <strong>cold water </strong>to the base of the air fryer<strong> </strong>(this will help steam the vegetables!)</p><p>Add the <strong>broccoli florets </strong>and <strong>onion petals </strong>to the air fryer<strong> </strong>basket with a generous spray of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min, shaking the basket occasionally, or until the veg is slightly charred and cooked through, then set aside for later</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675272413935-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675272413935-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675272413935-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675272413935-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675272413935-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the broccoli and onion are cooking, drain the <strong>tofu</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained tofu</strong> into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>tofu pieces</strong> to a large bowl with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>soy sauce </strong>and 3/4 of the <strong>cornflour</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and give everything a good mix up until all the tofu is coated – this is your <strong>coated tofu</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1675272418241-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1675272418241-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1675272418241-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1675272418241-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1675272418241-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>coated tofu</strong> to the air fryer basket<strong> </strong>with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and cook for 5-6 min, shaking the basket occasionally, or until golden and crispy</p><p>While the tofu is cooking, combine the the juice of the <strong>orange<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>in a small bowl with the <strong>remaining soy sauce </strong>and <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>remaining cornflour</strong>, 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and mix until fully combined – this is your <strong>orange sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
